[[Cambodia]] had a total primary energy supply ([[TPES]]) of 5.48 [[tonne of oil equivalent|Mtoe]] in 2012.<ref name=iea2012 /> Electricity consumption was 3.06 [[TWh]]. About one third of the energy came from oil products and about two thirds from biofuels and waste.<ref name=iea2012>{{cite web|title=Cambodia|url=http://www.iea.org/statistics/statisticssearch/report/?year=2012&country=Cambodia&product=Balances|website=www.iea.org|publisher=International Energy Agency (IEA)|accessdate=5 October 2015}}</ref>

